description.narrative: By August 2020, the prevalence of stunting among children is 30%; wasting is at 3% and severely wasted at 1% (-3 SD); 53% of children aged 6–8 months introduced timely to complementary feeding; 55 % of children 0-5 months exclusively breastmilk fed; 23% of children aged 6-23 months receive food that meets minimum dietary diversity while only 11% of them meet minimum acceptable diet. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:28/08/2020
